- Use `ng xi18n` to extract i18n messages from your Angular app.
- Update `angular.json` to include the `i18n` configuration:
  ```json
  "projects": {
    "your-project-name": {
      "architect": {
        "build": {
          "options": {
            "localize": ["en", "fr"]
          }
        },
        "serve": {
          "options": {
            "localize": ["en", "fr"]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  ```
- Use `ng serve --configuration=fr` to run your app in French.
- Translate messages using a translation service like Transifex or Crowdin.
- Update the `src/locale/messages.fr.xlf` file with translations.
- Build the app for production with `ng build --prod --localize`.
- Deploy the localized version of your app.
